---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Taylor Heathcote">
  <div class="split-grid">
    <section class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Thoughtful, creative, and quietly detail-obsessed.</h1>
      <p>
        I’m a creative generalist with a background in game design and a
        strong interest in structure, presentation, and player-facing
        experience. I like work that feels considered — visually,
        emotionally, and practically.
      </p>
      <p>
        My interests sit around design thinking, communication,
        organisation, narrative and systems ideas, and the kind of polish
        that makes a project feel coherent rather than stitched together at
        the last second.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Background</p>
      <h2>Education and focus</h2>
      <p>
        I completed a <strong>First-Class BSc in Game Design</strong> in
        2024. Through study and self-directed work, I’ve developed an
        interest in creative problem solving, design communication, project
        framing, and building experiences that feel intentional.
      </p>
      <p>
        I’m especially drawn to games and creative work with strong
        identity, thoughtful systems, and a clear sense of tone.
      </p>

      <div class="button-row">
        <a href="/" class="button button-primary">Back Home</a>
        <a href="/projects" class="button button-secondary">Projects Next</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>